title: Seattle Seahawks-Cincinnati Bengals: What to Watch
text:
Friday’s prep football results Originally published October 9, 2015 at 10:51 pm Updated October 9, 2015 at 10:54 pm Duncan Varela (Interlake) had 415 all-purpose yards and six touchdowns in a win over Mercer Island. By Pam London 
Interlake 48, Mercer Island 41 
Duncan Varela was 19-23 for 224 yards and four touchdowns and carried the ball 22 times for 191 yards and two touchdowns to lead Interlake over Mercer Island in a KingCo 2A/3A game. Varela also rushed for three two-point conversions in the victory. 
Sumner 42, Auburn 21 
Connor Wedington had 15 carries for 170 yards and three touchdowns and scored on a 54-yard punt return in Sumner’s SPSL 3A win over Auburn. Luke Ross was 10-11 for 135 yards for the Spartans. Most Read Stories
